WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.842 --> 00:00:11.845
“Can AI be trusted?”

00:00:12.262 --> 00:00:13.054
“Who’s gonna hit the brakes,

00:00:13.054 --> 00:00:14.848
if we need to?”

00:00:14.848 --> 00:00:16.474
“How do we really ensure that,

00:00:16.474 --> 00:00:17.517
what we’re aiming to achieve,

00:00:17.517 --> 00:00:18.768
really does,

00:00:18.768 --> 00:00:21.896
benefit the majority of people?”

00:00:23.148 --> 00:00:24.315
“If it ends up taking like

00:00:24.315 --> 00:00:25.400
almost all the jobs,

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:28.111
then what does it mean to work?”

00:00:29.446 --> 00:00:30.905
“But wait a minute,

00:00:30.905 --> 00:00:33.908
why do we have to have this stuff?”

00:00:34.367 --> 00:00:36.828
“If a machine can pretend to care,

00:00:36.828 --> 00:00:39.289
better than I can actually care,

00:00:39.414 --> 00:00:41.958
how do we draw the line there?”

00:00:41.958 --> 00:00:42.417
“If we all had a voice in it,

00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:43.418
“If we all had a voice in it,

00:00:43.418 --> 00:00:43.877
“If we all had a voice in it,

00:00:43.877 --> 00:00:46.463
then I feel like it would be better.”

00:00:46.463 --> 00:00:48.256
“Could AI help people

00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:50.592
stop feeling misunderstood?”

00:00:51.468 --> 00:00:53.261
“Could AI help me build

00:00:53.261 --> 00:00:56.973
more connections in the community?”

00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:58.850
“Can AI help me be a better,

00:00:58.850 --> 00:01:00.310
teacher, better mom?”

00:01:01.394 --> 00:01:03.563
“Maybe it’ll cure some great things,

00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:04.606
you know?”

00:01:04.606 --> 00:01:06.524
“Things that we're not even

00:01:06.524 --> 00:01:07.942
at the cusp of understanding yet.”

00:01:08.610 --> 00:01:11.112
“Will it create a group of people that,

00:01:11.112 --> 00:01:12.655
ask more questions?”

00:01:13.323 --> 00:01:14.157
“What if we started,

00:01:14.157 --> 00:01:15.909
to be more human again?”

00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:17.368
“We don’t want to lose

00:01:17.368 --> 00:01:19.370
the most beautiful parts of life.”
